@startmindmap
* Aiken on Cardano
** eUTXO model
*** Validator, not actor
*** f(datum, redeemer, context)
*** Returns Bool: approve or reject
*** Deterministic evaluation
** Language & target
*** Purpose-built for validators
*** Rust/Elm/Gleam syntax
*** Compiles to UPLC
*** Alternatives: Plinth, Plutarch, OpShin, Scalus, Marlowe
** Toolchain (single binary)
*** aiken new / build / check
*** Formatter + LSP
*** Built-in test runner
*** aikup version manager
** Validator anatomy (Plutus V3)
*** Handlers: spend, mint, withdraw
*** publish, vote, propose
*** else fallback (fail)
*** datum is Option in V3
** Parameters
*** Compile-time parameters
*** Unique policy id / address
*** One-shot minting policy
*** blueprint apply
** Testing
*** test keyword returns Bool
*** Property tests via Fuzzer
*** fail expectations
*** bench, reports ex-units
** Deploy artifact
*** CIP-57 plutus.json blueprint
*** blueprint address / policy / hash
*** Off-chain hand-off
*** Lucid / Mesh / PyCardano / Blaze
@endmindmap
